  "root_text": {
    "sn9.14:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 9.14 ",
    "sn9.14:0.2": "1. Vanavagga ",
    "sn9.14:0.3": "Gandhatthenasutta ",
    "sn9.14:1.1": "Ekaṁ samayaṁ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṁ vanasaṇḍe. ",
    "sn9.14:1.2": "Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu pacchābhattaṁ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto pokkharaṇiṁ ogāhetvā padumaṁ upasiṅghati. ",
    "sn9.14:1.3": "Atha kho yā tasmiṁ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno anukampikā atthakāmā taṁ bhikkhuṁ saṁvejetukāmā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṁ bhikkhuṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn9.14:2.1": "“Yametaṁ vārijaṁ pupphaṁ, ",
    "sn9.14:2.2": "adinnaṁ upasiṅghasi; ",
    "sn9.14:2.3": "Ekaṅgametaṁ theyyānaṁ, ",
    "sn9.14:2.4": "gandhatthenosi mārisā”ti. ",
    "sn9.14:3.1": "“Na harāmi na bhañjāmi, ",
    "sn9.14:3.2": "ārā siṅghāmi vārijaṁ; ",
    "sn9.14:3.3": "Atha kena nu vaṇṇena, ",
    "sn9.14:3.4": "gandhatthenoti vuccati. ",
    "sn9.14:4.1": "Yvāyaṁ bhisāni khanati, ",
    "sn9.14:4.2": "puṇḍarīkāni bhañjati; ",
    "sn9.14:4.3": "Evaṁ ākiṇṇakammanto, ",
    "sn9.14:4.4": "kasmā eso na vuccatī”ti. ",
    "sn9.14:5.1": "“Ākiṇṇaluddo puriso, ",
    "sn9.14:5.2": "dhāticelaṁva makkhito; ",
    "sn9.14:5.3": "Tasmiṁ me vacanaṁ natthi, ",
    "sn9.14:5.4": "tvañcārahāmi vattave. ",
    "sn9.14:6.1": "Anaṅgaṇassa posassa, ",
    "sn9.14:6.2": "niccaṁ sucigavesino; ",
    "sn9.14:6.3": "Vālaggamattaṁ pāpassa, ",
    "sn9.14:6.4": "abbhāmattaṁva khāyatī”ti. ",
    "sn9.14:7.1": "“Addhā maṁ yakkha jānāsi, ",
    "sn9.14:7.2": "atho me anukampasi; ",
    "sn9.14:7.3": "Punapi yakkha vajjāsi, ",
    "sn9.14:7.4": "yadā passasi edisan”ti. ",
    "sn9.14:8.1": "“Neva taṁ upajīvāma, ",
    "sn9.14:8.2": "napi te bhatakāmhase; ",
    "sn9.14:8.3": "Tvameva bhikkhu jāneyya, ",
    "sn9.14:8.4": "yena gaccheyya suggatin”ti. ",
    "sn9.14:9.1": "Atha kho so bhikkhu tāya devatāya saṁvejito saṁvegamāpādīti. ",
    "sn9.14:9.2": "Vanavaggo paṭhamo. ",
    "sn9.14:10.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn9.14:10.1": "Vivekaṁ upaṭṭhānañca, ",
    "sn9.14:10.2": "Kassapagottena sambahulā; ",
    "sn9.14:10.3": "Ānando anuruddho ca, ",
    "sn9.14:10.4": "Nāgadattañca kulagharaṇī. ",
    "sn9.14:11.1": "Vajjiputto ca vesālī, ",
    "sn9.14:11.2": "Sajjhāyena ayoniso; ",
    "sn9.14:11.3": "Majjhanhikālamhi pākatindriya—",
    "sn9.14:11.4": "Padumapupphena cuddasa bhaveti. ",
    "sn9.14:11.5": "Vanasaṁyuttaṁ samattaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn9.14:0.1": "Linked Discourses 9.14 ",
    "sn9.14:0.2": "1. In the Woods ",
    "sn9.14:0.3": "The Thief of Scent ",
    "sn9.14:1.1": "At one time one of the mendicants was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. ",
    "sn9.14:1.2": "Now at that time, after the meal, on their return from almsround, that mendicant plunged into a lotus pond and sniffed a pink lotus. ",
    "sn9.14:1.3": "The deity haunting that forest had sympathy for that mendicant, and wanted what’s best for them. So they approached that mendicant wanting to stir them up, and addressed them in verse: ",
    "sn9.14:2.1": "“This water flower has not been given. ",
    "sn9.14:2.2": "When you sniff it, ",
    "sn9.14:2.3": "this is one factor of theft. ",
    "sn9.14:2.4": "Good fellow, you are a thief of scent!” ",
    "sn9.14:3.1": "“I do not take, nor do I break; ",
    "sn9.14:3.2": "I sniff the water flower from afar. ",
    "sn9.14:3.3": "So how do you explain why ",
    "sn9.14:3.4": "you call me a thief of scent? ",
    "sn9.14:4.1": "Why don’t you accuse someone ",
    "sn9.14:4.2": "who does such vandalizing ",
    "sn9.14:4.3": "as digging up the roots, ",
    "sn9.14:4.4": "or breaking off the flowers?” ",
    "sn9.14:5.1": "“I have nothing to say ",
    "sn9.14:5.2": "to a person who is a crude vandal, ",
    "sn9.14:5.3": "soiled like a used nappy. ",
    "sn9.14:5.4": "You’re the one who deserves to be spoken to. ",
    "sn9.14:6.1": "To the man who has not a blemish ",
    "sn9.14:6.2": "who is always seeking purity, ",
    "sn9.14:6.3": "even a hair-tip of evil ",
    "sn9.14:6.4": "seems as big as a stormcloud.” ",
    "sn9.14:7.1": "“Indeed, O spirit, you understand me, ",
    "sn9.14:7.2": "and you empathize with me. ",
    "sn9.14:7.3": "Please speak to me again, ",
    "sn9.14:7.4": "whenever you see something like this.” ",
    "sn9.14:8.1": "“We are no dependent of yours, ",
    "sn9.14:8.2": "nor are we your servant. ",
    "sn9.14:8.3": "You yourself should know, mendicant, ",
    "sn9.14:8.4": "the way that leads to a good place.” ",
    "sn9.14:9.1": "Impelled by that deity, that mendicant was struck with a sense of urgency. ",
    "sn9.14:9.2": "",
    "sn9.14:10.1": "",
    "sn9.14:10.2": "",
    "sn9.14:10.3": "",
    "sn9.14:10.4": "",
    "sn9.14:11.1": "",
    "sn9.14:11.2": "",
    "sn9.14:11.3": "",
    "sn9.14:11.4": "",
    "sn9.14:11.5": "The Linked Discourses in the Forest are completed. "
  },
